properties.headline: Fire Weather Watch issued February 1 at 3:16AM MST until February 2 at 6:00PM MST by NWS Pueblo CO
properties.description:
...A Fire Weather Watch is in effect for Sunday afternoon for
gusty winds, low humidity and dry fuels, for fire weather zones
233 and 237 which includes eastern Las Animas and Baca Counties...

The National Weather Service in Pueblo has issued a Fire Weather
Watch for gusty winds, low relative humidity and dry fuels, which
is in effect Sunday afternoon.

* Affected Area...Fire Weather Zones 233 and 237.

* Winds...Southwest 15 to 20 mph with gusts up to 30 mph.

* Relative Humidity...As low as 10 percent.

* Impacts...Conditions may be favorable for the rapid ignition,
growth and spread of fires.
properties.instruction:
A Fire Weather Watch means that critical fire weather conditions
are forecast to occur. Listen for later forecasts and possible
Red Flag Warnings.

NWSheadline: FIRE WEATHER WATCH IN EFFECT SUNDAY AFTERNOON FOR GUSTY WINDS AND LOW RELATIVE HUMIDITY FOR FIRE WEATHER ZONES 233 AND 237
